(1297, 126, 'What is "R-squared"?', 'A radius', 'A measure of how well the regression model fits the data', 'A type of car', 'A math constant', 'B'),
(1298, 126, 'What is "Stochastic Gradient Descent"?', 'A fast gradient', 'An iteration of gradient descent that uses a single random sample per step', 'A fixed path', 'A manual update', 'B'),
(1299, 126, 'What is "AdaBoost"?', 'An advertisement', 'A popular boosting algorithm for creating an ensemble of weak learners', 'A speed booster', 'A gaming tool', 'B'),
(1300, 126, 'What is "XGBoost"?', 'A type of shoes', 'An optimized distributed gradient boosting library', 'A fast network', 'A social app', 'B'),
(1301, 83, 'What is the primary goal of Threat Modeling?', 'To write faster code', 'To identify and prioritize potential security risks in a system', 'To design a logo', 'To hire new developers', 'B'),
(1302, 83, 'Which of these is a popular Threat Modeling framework?', 'SWOT', 'STRIDE', 'AGILE', 'SCRUM', 'B'),
(1303, 83, 'In STRIDE, what does the "S" stand for?', 'Scaling', 'Spoofing', 'Scanning', 'Scripting', 'B'),
(1304, 83, 'In STRIDE, what does "Tampering" refer to?', 'Stealing a password', 'Unauthorized modification of data', 'Deleting a file', 'A physical break-in', 'B'),
(1305, 83, 'What is "Repudiation" in the context of security?', 'Denying an action took place', 'Breaking a computer', 'Sending an email', 'Updating software', 'A'),
(1306, 83, 'What does the "I" in STRIDE stand for?', 'Information Disclosure', 'Identity Management', 'Internal Routing', 'Intelligent Design', 'A'),
(1307, 83, 'What does "Denial of Service" (DoS) aim to do?', 'Steal data', 'Make a service unavailable to users', 'Change a password', 'Encrypt files', 'B'),
(1308, 83, 'What is "Elevation of Privilege"?', 'Getting a promotion', 'Gaining higher access rights than intended', 'Moving to a new office', 'Writing better code', 'B'),
(1309, 83, 'What is a "Data Flow Diagram" (DFD) used for in threat modeling?', 'Calculating speed', 'Visualizing how data moves through a system', 'Drawing a map', 'Sorting a list', 'B'),
(1310, 83, 'What is a "Trust Boundary" in a DFD?', 'A legal contract', 'A point where data transitions between different levels of trust', 'A firewall only', 'A physical wall', 'B'),
(1311, 83, 'Which methodology uses a "Threat Tree" approach?', 'DREAD', 'PASTA', 'STRIDE', 'OCTAVE', 'B'),
(1312, 83, 'What is the "DREAD" risk assessment model?', 'A horror movie', 'A system for rating threats based on Damage, Reproducibility, etc.', 'A coding standard', 'A network speed test', 'B'),
(1313, 83, 'In DREAD, what does "Reproducibility" measure?', 'How many children a threat has', 'How easy it is to repeat the attack', 'How fast the code runs', 'The size of the data', 'B'),
(1314, 83, 'What is "Attack Surface"?', 'The screen of the computer', 'The sum of all points where an attacker can enter or extract data', 'The keyboard layout', 'A type of desk', 'B'),
(1315, 83, 'What is a "Countermeasure"?', 'A tool for counting', 'An action or process that reduces a threat or vulnerability', 'A fast computer', 'A database index', 'B'),
(1316, 83, 'What is "Vulnerability"?', 'Being very strong', 'A weakness in a system that can be exploited', 'A fast network', 'A type of software', 'B'),
(1317, 83, 'What is a "Threat Actor"?', 'A movie star', 'An individual or group that performs a threat action', 'A system administrator', 'A customer', 'B'),
(1318, 83, 'What is "Risk" in a security context?', 'The cost of the PC', 'The probability of a threat occurring multiplied by its impact', 'A dangerous sport', 'A random event', 'B'),
(1319, 83, 'What is the "Microsoft Threat Modeling Tool"?', 'A word processor', 'A free tool to help create DFDs and identify threats', 'A virus scanner', 'A game engine', 'B'),
(1320, 83, 'What is "Asset" in threat modeling?', 'A personâs skill', 'Something of value that needs protection', 'A type of file', 'A computer mouse', 'B'),
(1321, 83, 'What is "Attack Tree"?', 'A tree in a park', 'A diagram showing the different ways an attacker can achieve a goal', 'A type of plant', 'A recursive function', 'B'),
(1322, 83, 'What is the "OCTAVE" methodology?', 'A musical scale', 'A framework for risk-based strategic assessment and planning', 'A type of hardware', 'A eight-step code', 'B'),
(1323, 83, 'What is "Entry Point" in a system?', 'A door', 'A specific location where data or users enter the application', 'A login button only', 'A network cable', 'B'),
(1324, 83, 'What is "Information Disclosure"?', 'Sharing news', 'Exposing sensitive data to unauthorized individuals', 'Printing a report', 'Writing a blog', 'B'),
(1325, 83, 'What is "Mitigation"?', 'Moving to another city', 'Reducing the severity or likelihood of a risk', 'Fixing a bug', 'Ignoring a problem', 'B'),
(1326, 83, 'What is "residual risk"?', 'The risk that remains after mitigation efforts', 'A small risk', 'A leftover file', 'A system error', 'A'),
(1327, 83, 'What is "Security by Design"?', 'Using pretty colors', 'Building security into the system from the start of development', 'Hiring a designer', 'Using a firewall', 'B'),
(1328, 83, 'What is a "Process" in a DFD?', 'A task at work', 'A task that handles or transforms data', 'A type of computer', 'A human worker', 'B'),
(1329, 83, 'What is "Data Store" in a DFD?', 'A retail shop', 'A place where data is kept (e.g., database, file)', 'A memory stick', 'A hard drive only', 'B'),
(1330, 83, 'What is "External Interactor" in a DFD?', 'A person outside', 'An entity outside the system that communicates with it', 'A web browser', 'A hacker', 'B'),
(1331, 83, 'What is "Threat Analysis"?', 'Reading the news', 'The process of understanding how threats can impact an organization', 'A math test', 'A code review', 'B'),
(1332, 83, 'What is "Zero Trust" architecture?', 'Not trusting anyone', 'A model that requires strict identity verification for everyone', 'A system with no security', 'A broken network', 'B'),
(1333, 83, 'What is "Least Privilege" principle?', 'Being poor', 'Giving a user only the access they need to perform their job', 'No access at all', 'Full admin access', 'B'),
(1334, 83, 'What is "Defense in Depth"?', 'Deep ocean diving', 'Using multiple layers of security controls', 'A thick firewall', 'A long password', 'B'),
(1335, 83, 'What is "Incident Response"?', 'Answering a phone', 'The process of managing a security breach', 'A type of game', 'A software update', 'B'),
(1336, 83, 'What is "Penetration Testing"?', 'Testing a pen', 'A simulated cyberattack to find vulnerabilities', 'Writing on paper', 'Testing network speed', 'B');
INSERT INTO `assessment_questions` (`id`, `node_id`, `question_text`, `option_a`, `option_b`, `option_c`, `option_d`, `correct_option`) VALUES
(1337, 83, 'What is "CVSS"?', 'Common Vulnerability Scoring System', 'Computer Virus Security Solution', 'Central Version Storage System', 'Code Validation Security Standard', 'A'),
(1338, 83, 'What is "Exploitability" in CVSS?', 'How easy it is to use a tool', 'A measure of how easy it is for an attacker to exploit a vulnerability', 'The cost of an attack', 'The speed of code', 'B'),
(1339, 83, 'What is "Impact" in risk assessment?', 'Hitting a ball', 'the degree of damage caused by a threat', 'A large file', 'A new feature', 'B'),
(1340, 83, 'What is "Threat Intelligence"?', 'Being smart about hackers', 'Evidence-based knowledge about existing or emerging threats', 'A security spy', 'A robot hacker', 'B'),
(1341, 120, 'What is "User Research"?', 'Searching for users', 'The practice of studying user behavior and needs to inform design', 'Hiring new employees', 'Selling a product', 'B'),
(1342, 120, 'What is a "User Persona"?', 'A real person', 'A fictional character representing a user segment', 'A profile picture', 'A system username', 'B'),
(1343, 120, 'What is the primary purpose of a Persona?', 'To name the users', 'To build empathy and focus design on real user goals', 'To increase sales', 'To track user location', 'B'),
(1344, 120, 'What is "Qualitative Research"?', 'Research with numbers', 'Research focused on understanding "why" and "how" through observations', 'Researching quality', 'A type of survey', 'B'),
(1345, 120, 'What is "Quantitative Research"?', 'Research focused on numerical data and "how many"', 'Research about quantity', 'Asking for opinions', 'Drawing pictures', 'A'),
(1346, 120, 'What is an "Empathy Map"?', 'A map of a city', 'A tool to visualize what users say, do, think, and feel', 'A map of the brain', 'A social network', 'B'),
(1347, 120, 'What is "Usability Testing"?', 'Testing if a tool works', 'Evaluating a product by testing it with representative users', 'Testing the code', 'A speed test', 'B'),
(1348, 120, 'What is a "Pain Point"?', 'A physical injury', 'A specific problem that users encounter', 'A sharp object', 'A low battery', 'B'),
(1349, 120, 'What is "User Journey Mapping"?', 'Tracking a traveler', 'Visualizing the process a person goes through to accomplish a goal', 'Drawing a line', 'A GPS coordinate', 'B'),
(1350, 120, 'What is "Contextual Inquiry"?', 'Asking questions in an office', 'An interview technique where researchers observe users in their natural environment', 'A secret investigation', 'A quick survey', 'B'),
(1351, 120, 'What is "Card Sorting" used for?', 'Playing games', 'Designing the information architecture of a website', 'Cleaning a desk', 'Sorting credit cards', 'B'),
(1352, 120, 'What is "A/B Testing"?', 'A school test', 'Comparing two versions of a webpage to see which performs better', 'Testing a battery', 'An alphabet game', 'B'),
(1353, 120, 'What is "Stakeholder Interview"?', 'Talking to a boss', 'Interviewing people with an interest in the project to understand goals', 'Talking to a neighbor', 'A job interview', 'B'),
(1354, 120, 'What is "Heuristic Evaluation"?', 'A medical test', 'A usability inspection method where experts judge a design against principles', 'A fast calculation', 'A type of code', 'B'),
(1355, 120, 'What is "Accessibility" in UX?', 'Opening a door', 'Designing products so they can be used by everyone, including those with disabilities', 'A fast internet', 'A cheap price', 'B'),
(1356, 120, 'What is "Mental Model"?', 'A 3D brain model', 'What a user believes to be true about how a system works', 'A smart idea', 'A memory game', 'B'),
(1357, 120, 'What is "Focus Group"?', 'A group of friends', 'A small group of people discussed together for market research', 'A camera lens', 'A concentrated team', 'B'),
(1358, 120, 'What is a "Proto-Persona"?', 'A very old persona', 'A persona based on team assumptions rather than new research', 'A prototype', 'A robot persona', 'B'),
(1359, 120, 'What is "Survey" in research?', 'Looking at a view', 'A method for collecting data from a pre-defined group of people', 'A type of map', 'A property check', 'B'),
(1360, 120, 'What is "Bias" in user research?', 'An unfair opinion', 'When the researcherâs presence or questioning influences the results', 'A coding error', 'A system delay', 'B'),
(1361, 120, 'What is "Ethnographic Research"?', 'Research on ethnicity', 'Studying people in their own environment through observation and interviews', 'A historical study', 'A type of map', 'B'),
(1362, 120, 'What is "User Flow"?', 'Water moving in a pipe', 'The path taken by a typical user on a website to complete a task', 'A fast download', 'A social media feed', 'B'),
(1363, 120, 'What is "Information Architecture"?', 'Building a library', 'The structural design of shared information environments', 'A hard drive', 'A website code', 'B'),
(1364, 120, 'What is "Touchpoint"?', 'A physical button', 'Any point of interaction between a user and a brand/product', 'A screen tap', 'A finger print', 'B'),
(1365, 120, 'What is "Scenario" in UX?', 'A movie scene', 'A narrative describing a userâs interaction with a product', 'A background image', 'A project plan', 'B'),
(1366, 120, 'What is "Affinity Mapping"?', 'Drawing a map of friends', 'A process used to organize information into logical groups', 'A math graph', 'A type of color', 'B'),
(1367, 120, 'What is "User Needs"?', 'Things users want to buy', 'Functional or emotional requirements users have to reach a goal', 'Asking for money', 'A list of tools', 'B'),
(1368, 120, 'What is "Prototype"?', 'A finished product', 'A preliminary model of a product to test concepts', 'A broken app', 'A coding manual', 'B'),
(1369, 120, 'What is "Eye Tracking"?', 'Looking at someone', 'Measuring where a person is looking and for how long', 'A medical exam', 'A surveillance tool', 'B'),
(1370, 120, 'What is "Cognitive Walkthrough"?', 'Walking and thinking', 'A task-based usability method where experts evaluate the ease of learning', 'A long hike', 'A memory test', 'B'),
(1371, 120, 'What is "Remote Research"?', 'Research on TV remotes', 'User research conducted without being physically present with the user', 'An isolated study', 'A long distance call', 'B'),
(1372, 120, 'What is "Diary Study"?', 'Reading a diary', 'A research method where participants log their activities over a period of time', 'A school project', 'A secret note', 'B'),
(1373, 120, 'What is "Task Analysis"?', 'Doing homework', 'The process of learning about ordinary users by observing them in action', 'A list of chores', 'A code review', 'B'),
(1374, 120, 'What is "Behavioral Data"?', 'A childâs report', 'Data about how users actually interact with a product', 'A psychological test', 'A system log', 'B'),
(1375, 120, 'What is "Attitudinal Data"?', 'Feeling angry', 'Data about what users say or how they feel', 'A loud noise', 'A type of survey', 'B'),
(1376, 120, 'What is "Demographics"?', 'A scary group', 'Statistical data relating to the population and particular groups', 'A type of graph', 'A map of a town', 'B'),
(1377, 120, 'What is "Recruitment" in research?', 'Hiring soldiers', 'The process of finding and selecting participants for a study', 'A job search', 'A marketing ad', 'B'),
(1378, 120, 'What is "Moderated Testing"?', 'Testing in moderation', 'A usability test where a facilitator guides the participant', 'A controlled experiment', 'A silent test', 'B'),
(1379, 120, 'What is "Unmoderated Testing"?', 'A wild test', 'A test where participants complete tasks on their own without guidance', 'A broken test', 'A quick check', 'B'),
(1380, 120, 'What is "Insight" in research?', 'Looking inside', 'A clear, deep understanding of a userâs behavior or motivation', 'A hidden secret', 'A bright light', 'B');
